  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Pentoxifylline improves microcirculation and decreases TNF alpha levels associated with
      sepsis, rendering it of potential therapeutic value in necrotizing enterocolitis in premature
      neonates.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Preterm neonates with a clinical suspicion of necrotizing enterocolitis (NEC) will
      potentially be candidates for study. After obtaining parental consent, the infants will be
      prospectively and randomly assigned to one of two groups: 1. Treatment group: to receive IV
      pentoxifylline (5 mg/kg/hour to run over 6 hour x 6 days) and 2. Placebo group: to receive an
      equal volume of Â½ normal saline to run over 6 hours x 6 days.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
