  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>To demonstrate that fewer of the babies who are treated with PTX will progress to serious NEC related morbidity, ie. perforation, surgery [including peritoneal drain placement], and/or death related to NEC.</measure>
    <time_frame>Three years</time_frame>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>To demonstrate lower levels of TNF alpha,fecal calprotectin;Improved SMA blood flow;Quicker radiographic resolution; Decreased feeding intolerance after acute NEC episode; and lower NEC associated long term morbidity.</measure>
    <time_frame>Three years</time_frame>
  </secondary_outcome>
